result.formatted_address: Langham Place Shopping Mall, 8 Argyle St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Genki Sushi

reviews.text: Taste is good, service is good, but need to wait over 10 minutes in the weekends

It's a sushi chain for sure so it might be strange to rate one a shop over another. This shop was a very very busy one and travelers take note. They have an app for ordering which if your country of residence is not Hong Kong you are unable to download from Google Play. Thus you are limited to using the paper ordering system, because many of the seats are actually not next to the conveyor belt. 
Using this system it took just over 20 minutes for our sushi to arrive. Because they cannot take plates off the conveyor system for us apparently.
The sushi itself the rice is made by machines and evidently it's not set properly. When you pick sushi up using chopsticks the fish falls off the top and the rice itself crumbles. This did not happen at the other Genki sushi shop. So in the end after being starved for over 20 minutes we were struggling to eat the sushi because it was falling apart before we could get it to our mouths.
And given the 20 minute wait we could not order anything else because we didn't have time.
Decent food. Great location. Ok service.
Typical inexpensive conveyor belt sushi restaurant. Their Uni was pretty bad

I love the sushi here! I'm not an expert but its better than the ones back home. The trains that transport the sushi in front of you are so cute, please could you make it international because i want one back home rather than the conveyor belt :D
